      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>23 threads, <a href=item.html?item=3800&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102427395854384></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102427395854384><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3800&mid=102427395854384>Monk Only?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3800&mid=102427395854384#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=162930><span id= >sabarazz</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 16th 8:41 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Determining who gets these in a group shouldn't be that difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are a few (COMMON SENSE) rules to keep in mind though.  Sure, the 0.0 wt is outstanding!  Who wouldn't want to wear an all/all 10ac +stats with 0.0 wt?  If there happens to be a lot of loot. . . loot that a monk can't grab due to his/her wt restriction. . . then go ahead and let em have it. . . but. . . if it's been fair game all game. . .everyone should roll on it.  I'm a Monk of the 27th Scale. . and when I loot something better than what I have. . .I keep the slightly lesser stuff for trade purposes later on. . . . granted that run to the bank might be tedious. . . . but you can work something our for later in the game.  .. . that's what tells are for.  This happens to be my first and only character .. . . and I would love to get a hold of any spider fur anything. . . but if I'm  in a group. . . let's face it. . most people in my groups all have a need for it.  I am a non-tweaked character that's had to punch kick and claw my way to where I am at. . . . but I also understand that at some point. . . so did almost everyone else that plays this GAME.  If I happen to have an unlucky roll once in a while. . . .I will roll on something another party member needs.  ..and then if I win. . work out a trade.  Common Sense.  Keep in mind also, that this is still just a game.  It is addictive (I'm hooked for life!) it can be frustrating.  .but never lose sight that it's still a game.  Have fun with it.  <br>&nbsp;<br><br>Sabarazz Swiftfists<br>Monk of the 27th Scale</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
